Package: SpaMixed
Type: Package
Title: Spatial mixed models for assessing environmental exposure effects on the microbiome (SpaMixed)
Version: 1.0
Date: 2026-05-22
Author: Sooran Kim
Maintainer: Sooran Kim <Sooran.Kim@nyulangone.org>
Description: The package fits zero-inflated Poisson model for
    high-dimensional microbiome data while accounting for spatial dependence among
    subjects' regions and dependence among microbial taxa. The package includes utilities
    for preprocessing microbiome count data, constructing taxon-level neighborhood matrices, 	 fitting models with INLA, and identifying exposure-associated
    taxa using local false discovery rate.
